The press briefing covered various topics, including the opioid crisis, the recent chemical weapons attack in Syria, and the President's stance on Russia. The White House expressed its commitment to addressing the opioid crisis and ensuring the safety of American streets. Regarding the chemical weapons attack in Syria, the President has been briefed by his national security team and is confident in his statements about it. The White House called on the international community to hold the perpetrators accountable and for Syria and Russia to allow international assistance and monitoring. The briefing also touched on the President's desire to bring troops home from Syria after defeating ISIS, but also to deter Assad from using chemical weapons. The White House emphasized that the President has been tough on Russia and that his actions reflect that. Other topics discussed included Scott Pruitt's actions at the EPA and the upcoming testimony of Mark Zuckerberg before Congress.